      <h2>Solar and Battery Systems for Commercial Buildings</h2>
      <p>
        Commercial buildings have different energy demands to homes — higher consumption, three-phase power, demand charges, and operating schedules that don't align with solar generation. A residential-grade solar system won't cut it.
      </p>
      <p>
        EES designs and installs commercial solar and battery systems that address these challenges directly — reducing operating costs, cutting peak demand charges, and moving your building toward lower energy bills.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Install</h2>

      <h3><a href="/services/commercial/solar-systems">Commercial Solar Systems</a></h3>
      <p>
        Rooftop and ground-mount solar for offices, retail, warehouses, medical centres, aged care, and industrial buildings. We design three-phase systems from 30 kW to 100+ kW, optimised for your load profile and roof layout. Commercial solar delivers strong ROI through reduced electricity bills, Small-scale Technology Certificates (STCs), and accelerated tax depreciation under Division 40.
      </p>

      <h3><a href="/services/commercial/battery-systems">Commercial Battery Storage</a></h3>
      <p>
        Behind-the-meter battery storage for peak demand reduction, demand charge management, and energy arbitrage. Commercial batteries shave your peak demand — which is often the largest component of a business electricity bill — and provide backup power for critical loads. Systems can be configured for grid services and virtual power plant participation.
      </p>

      <h2>Why Commercial Clients Choose EES</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Integrated design</strong> — we design solar and battery as one system, not separate contracts with separate trades</li>
        <li><strong>We install what we design</strong> — CEC-accredited electricians install every system. No subcontractors</li>
        <li><strong>Local support</strong> — we're based in Moolap, Geelong, and provide ongoing monitoring and maintenance</li>
        <li><strong>10-year workmanship warranty</strong> — on every commercial installation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Industries We Work With</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Offices and commercial buildings</strong> — reduce operating costs and meet sustainability targets</li>
        <li><strong>Retail and hospitality</strong> — lower energy bills with solar self-consumption</li>
        <li><strong>Medical and healthcare</strong> — reliable power with battery backup for critical loads</li>
        <li><strong>Warehouses and industrial</strong> — large-scale solar and battery for demand charge reduction</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-residential developments</strong> — centralised solar and battery for apartments and townhouse complexes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Financial Benefits</h2>
      <p>
        Commercial solar and battery systems deliver returns through multiple channels:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Reduced electricity bills</strong> — solar self-consumption offsets grid purchases at retail rates</li>
        <li><strong>Peak demand reduction</strong> — batteries shave demand charges, often the largest bill component</li>
        <li><strong>STCs and rebates</strong> — Small-scale Technology Certificates reduce upfront costs</li>
        <li><strong>Tax depreciation</strong> — commercial solar and battery assets can be depreciated under Division 40</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Work</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Site assessment</strong> — we review your building, energy bills, load profile, and operating schedule</li>
        <li><strong>System design</strong> — we design a solar and battery system addressing your specific energy challenges</li>
        <li><strong>Proposal</strong> — detailed proposal with system specs, pricing, projected savings, and ROI timeline</li>
        <li><strong>Installation</strong> — our team installs with minimal disruption to your operations</li>
        <li><strong>Commissioning and monitoring</strong> — we commission the system, configure monitoring, and provide ongoing support</li>
      </ol>

